overview: The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for data
  access, and an authentication system. The agent successfully implemented a
  Prisma-based PostgreSQL database schema, API endpoints for data management
  (including CSV export), and a client-facing admin dashboard. A key decision
  involved simplifying the authentication from a custom HMAC-signed session
  system to a more straightforward Next.js middleware-based approach, which
  improved code clarity and efficiency for the specified use case. The database
  was set up using NeonDB, and the agent guided the user through the necessary
  environment variable configuration and Prisma migrations. The implementation
  is currently being tested, with a minor hiccup identified where the "Pre-fill
  & Jump to Report" button did not trigger the database save, which the agent is
  now addressing by re-testing the full submission process.
